The street came alive in '75. On a super stage a band of brothers in blood and spirit gathered the grooves of
Sly Stone, the inner vision of Stevie Wonder and the searching message of Marvin Gaye and blew them out to a hungry public. They fed them with the right to be mighty and invited them to share a happy feeling. Here on stage was the way of their world and a window of what our world could be. This is your ticket to a concert now playing for a new generation.
Turn up the flame and feel the eternal fire....

Happy feelings everybody....

